## GitHub Secrets — Why and How
### Why Secrets?
```
❌ WRONG - Putting password in code:
username: chandangadewar
password: mypassword123
↑ Anyone can see this on GitHub!
↑ Hackers can steal your Docker Hub account!
✅ RIGHT - Using secrets:
username: ${{ secrets.DOCKER_USERNAME }}
password: ${{ secrets.DOCKER_PASSWORD }}
↑ Password stored safely in GitHub
↑ Never visible in code
↑ Only used during workflow run
```

### How Secrets Work:
```
You add secret in GitHub Settings
        ↓
GitHub encrypts and stores it
        ↓
During workflow, GitHub decrypts it
        ↓
Used in the workflow step
        ↓
Never visible in logs or code
```

