## Problems You Faced & What You Learned
### Problem 1 — Dockerfile not found
```
Error: failed to read dockerfile: open Dockerfile
       no such file or directory
Why it happened:
workflow said dockerfile: ./docker/backend/Dockerfile
but correct key is  file: ./docker/backend/Dockerfile
What you learned:
→ GitHub Actions uses exact parameter names
→ dockerfile: is wrong, file: is correct
```
### Problem 2 — react-scripts permission denied
```
Error: sh: 1: react-scripts: Permission denied
Why it happened:
→ npm install creates react-scripts with permissions
→ COPY . . command overwrites those permissions
→ react-scripts loses execute permission
What you learned:
→ Always chmod +x AFTER COPY command
→ File permissions matter in Linux/Docker
→ Windows doesn't care about permissions
  but Linux does!
```
### Problem 3 — Everything up to date
```
git push
→ Everything up-to-date (no workflow triggered!)
Why it happened:
→ No new commit was made
→ GitHub only triggers on NEW commits

What you learned:
→ Always do git add → git commit → git push
→ Never skip git commit step!
→ git commit --allow-empty forces empty commit

